## 2. V1 VS LATER-RELEASE SPLIT

### MVP (V1) - Core RAG + Local MCP

**In V1:**
- ✅ Basic embedding + vector store abstraction (interface only, mock implementation)
- ✅ Simple file ingestion (markdown, text, PDF via external tool)
- ✅ BM25 + embedding-based retrieval (hybrid)
- ✅ Single local MCP server support (browser automation)
- ✅ Metric collection (recall@K, precision, latency)
- ✅ File-based storage (SQLite + local vector DB mock)
- ✅ Environment-based config (`.env`, no secrets.json)
- ✅ QA test harness integration
- ✅ Basic observability (structured logging)

**NOT in V1:**
- ❌ Distributed MCP coordination
- ❌ Multi-modal RAG (images, tables)
- ❌ Advanced reranking backends
- ❌ Production vector DB integrations
- ❌ Fine-tuning / domain-specific models
- ❌ Streaming responses
- ❌ Cache invalidation strategies
- ❌ Advanced trace collection (distributed tracing)

### V2+ Enhancements

- Advanced MCP server composition (multiple servers, federation)
- Real-time streaming indexing
- Ray/distributed ingestion
