## 7. RISKS TO AVOID

### 🚨 Architecture Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| **Vendor lock-in on embeddings** | Abstraction layer + mock adapter; design for swappable backends from day 1 |
| **MCP server lifecycle hell** | Session pool + connection retry logic; test against crashes |
| **Coupling RAG to QA framework** | Separate `RagPlatform` from `TestRunner`; use event-driven communication |
| **Retrieval becomes bottleneck** | Benchmark early; add caching layer (v2); profile before optimizing |
| **Browser automation flakiness** | Deterministic waits (not sleeps); retry strategies; screenshot on failure |
| **Config explosion** | Strict schema validation; no free-form config; versioned config format |

### 🚨 Data & Integration Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| **Stale/hallucinated ground truth** | Version gold standard; tag with date; periodic refresh process |
| **MCP server incompatibilities** | Define MCP version ranges; test against multiple server impls |
| **Document ingestion data loss** | Transaction-like ingestion (all-or-nothing); audit logs; checkpointing |
| **Secrets in logs** | Sanitizer middleware; mask API keys; rotate often |
| **Evaluation metric gaming** | Multiple complementary metrics; manual spot-checks; user feedback loop |

### 🚨 Operational Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| **No observability during outage** | Structured logging; error tracking (Sentry); health checks |
| **Evaluation gaps** | Start with synthetic tests; add real user QA feedback; track false negatives |
| **Missing failure modes** | Chaos engineering (v2+); simulate MCP disconnects; test partial ingestion |
| **Configuration drift** | Deterministic config loading; config-as-code; track changes in git |
| **Unattended browser processes** | Resource limits; session timeout; process cleanup on error |

### 🚨 Development Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| **Premature optimization** | Start with mock backends; avoid "clean" architecture paralysis |
| **Over-engineering MCP** | Start with single browser server; defer federation to v2 |
| **No abstraction test coverage** | Mock all external services; integration tests against real services separately |
| **Evaluation bias** | Build human feedback loop early; don't just optimize for BLEU/ROUGE |
| **Documentation lag** | Document architecture decisions (ADRs); auto-generate from code |

